Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on cyber-physical attacks and threat models. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with Cyber-Physical Systems and their modeling. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses formal methods to reason about CPSs and attacks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of successful attacks on CPSs and possible quantifications of success chances. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still relevant as the paper defines a hybrid process calculus to model CPSs and attacks.
